ss a letter: E\" -> shows state with `_ _ _ _ E _` -> \"Good guess!\"\n\nSo E is in position 5 only, which matches GARDEN where E is position 5. So the word IS GARDEN. Let me continue reading:\n\n5. Guess \"Guess a letter: G\" -> \"No match\" (but G should match!)\n6. Guess \"Guess a letter: N\" -> \"No match\" (but N should match!)\n7. Guess \"Guess a letter: R\" -> \"Good guess!\" with `_ _ _ _ E R`\n\nBut this doesn't make sense. If G and N were guessed as wrong, but the final display shows positions, something is off. Actually wait - position 6 shows R, not N. So the order must be wrong. Let me just look at the final output and work backwards. The word displayed is `_ _ _ _ E R` and we guessed correctly for E and R. E is position 5 in GARDEN, but R is position 3, not position 6. So the word can't be GARDEN!\n\nUnless... wait, let me check if maybe the second new_game() call in main() uses a different seed value because the RNG state changed:\n\nOh! I think I see the issue. My seeded_choice function always creates `random.Random(42)` fresh, so it doesn't advance state. But that means every call returns the same word! Let me verify:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":960,"cache_read_input_tokens":62421,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":960},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"802dcc07-f06a-4920-82f9-0be55de92fb4","uuid":"ed29bf08-b888-4c9a-8f73-e4f4971d3541","request_id":"req_011CbxgTzi8KaX3mwc12dePU"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_016j6zsbPv1NxJmebUSqrYgD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Lj7kJk4fZnvkk6grEoqce9","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport random\n\ndef seeded_choice(seq):\n    rng = random.Random(42)\n    return rng.choice(seq)\n\nfrom word_garden import words\n\nresults = []\nfor i in range(3):\n    result = seeded_choice(words.WORDS)\n    results.append(result)\n    print(f\"Call {i+1}: {result}\")\n\nprint(f\"All same: {len(set(results)) == 1}\")\nPYEOF\n","description":"Check if seeded_choice is deterministic"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":960,"cache_read_input_tokens":62421,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":960},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"802dcc07-f06a-4920-82f9-0be55de92fb4","uuid":"30fec9b3-6a70-4e3f-8078-2b84e144bc39","request_id":"req_011CbxgTzi8KaX3mwc12dePU"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Lj7kJk4fZnvkk6grEoqce9","type":"tool_result","content":"Call 1: FLOWER\nCall 2: FLOWER\nCall 3: FLOWER\nAll same: True","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"802dcc07-f06a-4920-82f9-0be55de92fb4","uuid":"40d8c646-d80c-4488-af86-ec3f39353b36","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:47:56.342Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"Call 1: FLOWER\nCall 2: FLOWER\nCall 3: FLOWER\nAll same: True","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_013VwaajqaUQPmk3jbmsrgNY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hmm, it returns FLOWER, not GARDEN. But earlier my test showed GARDEN. Let me check what's different:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":958,"cache_read_input_tokens":63381,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":958},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"802dcc07-f06a-4920-82f9-0be55de92fb4","uuid":"cc970de1-53a4-496c-9150-970d9831617b","request_id":"req_011CbxgUfKbALMB9ZKUth5Ea"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_013VwaajqaUQPmk3jbmsrgNY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QxdYgbFxYdjiExi8cj7zZ4","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport random\n\n# First test what words.select_word returns\nfrom word_garden import words\n\nprint(\"WORDS list:\", words.WORDS)\n\nrng = random.Random(42)\nword1 = rng.choice(words.WORDS)\nprint(f\"rng.choice with seed 42: {word1}\")\n\n# Now test with easy difficulty pool\ncfg = words._DIFFICULTY_CONFIG[\"easy\"]\npool = [\n    w for w in words.WORDS\n    if len(w) >= cfg[\"min_len\"]\n    and (cfg[\"max_len\"] is None or len(w) <= cfg[\"max_len\"])\n]\nprint(f\"Easy pool: {pool}\")\n\nrng2 = random.Random(42)\nword2 = rng2.choice(pool)\nprint(f\"rng.choice from easy pool with seed 42: {word2}\")\nPYEOF\n","description":"Check pool filtering"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":958,"cache_read_input_tokens":63381,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":958},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"802dcc07-f06a-4920-82f9-0be55de92fb4","uuid":"fca70c28-22a7-4126-b48f-7ccce4cfea8a","request_id":"req_011CbxgUfKbALMB9ZKUth5Ea"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QxdYgbFxYdjiExi8cj7zZ4","type":"tool_result","content":"WORDS list: ['GARDEN', 'FLOWER', 'PLANET', 'PYTHON', 'TERMINAL', 'MEADOW', 'ORCHARD', 'VINEYARD', 'SEEDLING', 'HARVEST']\nrng.choice with seed 42: FLOWER\nEasy pool: ['GARDEN', 'FLOWER', 'PLANET', 'PYTHON', 'MEADOW']\nrng.choice from easy pool with seed 42: GARDEN","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"802dcc07-f06a-4920-82f9-0be55de92fb4","uuid":"42a13817-8643-4590-b40f-040a36877c2f","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:48:03.377Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"WORDS list: ['GARDEN', 'FLOWER', 'PLANET', 'PYTHON', 'TERMINAL', 'MEADOW', 'ORCHARD', 'VINEYARD', 'SEEDLING', 'HARVEST']\nrng.choice with seed 42: FLOWER\nEasy pool: ['GARDEN', 'FLOWER', 'PLANET', 'PYTHON', 'MEADOW']\nrng.choice from easy pool with seed 42: GARDEN","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01DKxgbNVjzqzibHoWYRambQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ah! There's the difference. When selecting from the full WORDS list, seed 42 gives FLOWER. When selecting from the easy pool, seed 42 gives GARDEN. So in the test, I'm calling `new_game(\"easy\")` but my seeded_choice doesn't know about the filtering. It just chooses from whatever list is passed to it.\n\nSo the seeded_choice is being called with the filtered easy pool, which has GARDEN as the result. Good. So the word should be GARDEN. Let me trace through the test one more time, now knowing the word is GARDEN:\n\nThe test guesses: A, D, E, G, N, R (in that order, since we sort them alphabetically).\n\nFor GARDEN:\n- A (position 2): matches, display becomes `_ A _ _ _ _`\n- D (position 4): matches, display becomes `_ A _ D _ _`\n- E (position 5): matches, display becomes `_ A _ D E _`\n- G (position 1): matches, display becomes `G A _ D E _`\n- N (position 6): matches, display becomes `G A _ D E N`\n- R (position 3): matches, display becomes `G A R D E N` -> WIN!\n\nBut the test output shows:\n- A: \"No match\"\n- D: \"No match\"\n- E: \"Good guess!\" -> `_ _ _ _ E _` (but this should be position 5, and A, D should have already been guessed and positions 2, 4 revealed!)\n\nSomething is wrong with my seeded_choice. Let me check - is it being called differently by the main() function?\n\nActually, wait. I think the issue is that main() is called with the seeded random.choice, but each call to main() will create a NEW new_game, which means choose() is called again, and since it's the same seed, it returns the same word. But that's not the problem.\n\nWait, I need to look at the test more carefully. Let me re-run the test and see what word is actually selected:\n\nActually, I think the problem is simpler - the test result shows that we're running the test with \"easy\" difficulty, but the word shown is different than the word in the state we created. Let me check if there's an issue with how the test is being run. Let me simplify the test for now and just make sure it passes basic checks:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":446,"cache_read_input_tokens":64339,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":446},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"802dcc07-f06a-4920-82f9-0be55de92fb4","uuid":"7b7788c6-9f4d-4b86-a094-db02343eacfe","request_id":"req_011CbxgVAUn4gQS4tSNCyYPX"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01DKxgbNVjzqzibHoWYRambQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JJpXsc547TNHuSdXyvAEED","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w1/tests/test_ui.py","old_string":"class TestMainEndToEndWin(unittest.TestCase):\n    \"\"\"Test a full game loop that ends in a win.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_end_to_end_win(self):\n        \"\"\"E2E: scripted win game shows final screen.\"\"\"\n        import word_garden.words as words_module\n\n        original_choice = random.choice\n\n        def seeded_choice(seq):\n            rng = random.Random(42)\n            return rng.choice(seq)\n\n        random.choice = seeded_choice\n        try:\n            state = new_game(\"easy\")\n            guesses = sorted(set(state.secret_word))\n\n            outputs = []\n            guess_iter = iter(guesses)\n\n            def fake_input():\n                try:\n                    return next(guess_iter)\n                except StopIteration:\n                    raise EOFError()\n\n            def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n                outputs.append(text + end)\n\n            result = main([\"--difficulty\", \"easy\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n\n            self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n            output_str = \"\".join(outputs)\n            self.assertIn(\"🌻 Bloom!\", output_str)\n            self.assertIn(\"The garden is thriving.\", output_str)\n        finally:\n            random.choice = original_choice\n\n    def test_end_to_end_win_ascii(self):\n        \"\"\"E2E: scripted win game in ASCII mode.\"\"\"\n        original_choice = random.choice\n\n        def seeded_choice(seq):\n            rng = random.Random(42)\n            return rng.choice(seq)\n\n        random.choice = seeded_choice\n        try:\n            state = new_game(\"easy\")\n            guesses = sorted(set(state.secret_word))\n\n            outputs = []\n            guess_iter = iter(guesses)\n\n            def fake_input():\n                try:\n                    return next(guess_iter)\n                except StopIteration:\n                    raise EOFError()\n\n            def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n                outputs.append(text + end)\n\n            result = main([\"--ascii\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n\n            self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n            output_str = \"\".join(outputs)\n            self.assertNotIn(\"💧\", output_str)\n            self.assertNotIn(\"🌻\", output_str)\n            self.assertIn(\"* Bloom!\", output_str)\n        finally:\n            random.choice = original_choice","new_string":"class TestMainEndToEndWin(unittest.TestCase):\n    \"\"\"Test a full game loop that ends in a win.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_end_to_end_win(self):\n        \"\"\"E2E: scripted win game shows final screen.\"\"\"\n        outputs = []\n\n        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n            outputs.append(text)\n\n        def fake_input_gen():\n            all_letters = \"ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ\"\n            for letter in all_letters:\n                yield letter\n\n        inputs = fake_input_gen()\n\n        def fake_input():\n            try:\n                letter = next(inputs)\n                return letter\n            except StopIteration:\n                raise EOFError()\n\n        result = main([\"--difficulty\", \"easy\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n\n        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n        output_str = \"\\n\".join(outputs)\n        self.assertIn(\"🌻 Bloom!\", output_str)\n        self.assertIn(\"The garden is thriving.\", output_str)\n\n    def test_end_to_end_win_ascii(self):\n        \"\"\"E2E: scripted win game in ASCII mode.\"\"\"\n        outputs = []\n\n        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n            outputs.append(text)\n\n        def fake_input_gen():\n            all_letters = \"ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ\"\n            for letter in all_letters:\n                yield letter\n\n        inputs = fake_input_gen()\n\n        def fake_input():\n            try:\n                letter = next(inputs)\n                return letter\n            except StopIteration:\n                raise EOFError()\n\n        result = main([\"--ascii\", \"--difficulty\", \"easy\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n\n        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n        output_str = \"\\n\".join(outputs)\n        self.assertNotIn(\"💧\", output_str)\n        self.assertNotIn(\"🌻\", output_str)\n        self.assertIn(\"* Bloom!\", output_str)"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":446,"cache_read_input_tokens":64339,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":446},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"802dcc07-f06a-4920-82f9-0be55de92fb4","uuid":"b6ab9c56-52d3-4872-a6a1-faf38feea240","request_id":"req_011CbxgVAUn4gQS4tSNCyYPX"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JJpXsc547TNHuSdXyvAEED","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w1/tests/test_ui.py has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"802dcc07-f06a-4920-82f9-0be55de92fb4","uuid":"5b8eb577-91f7-4c9f-b4f5-2333a865d44f","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:48:16.625Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w1/tests/test_ui.py","oldString":"class TestMainEndToEndWin(unittest.TestCase):\n    \"\"\"Test a full game loop that ends in a win.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_end_to_end_win(self):\n        \"\"\"E2E: scripted win game shows final screen.\"\"\"\n        import word_garden.words as words_module\n\n        original_choice = random.choice\n\n        def seeded_choice(seq):\n            rng = random.Random(42)\n            return rng.choice(seq)\n\n        random.choice = seeded_choice\n        try:\n            state = new_game(\"easy\")\n            guesses = sorted(set(state.secret_word))\n\n            outputs = []\n            guess_iter = iter(guesses)\n\n            def fake_input():\n                try:\n                    return next(guess_iter)\n                except StopIteration:\n                    raise EOFError()\n\n            def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n                outputs.append(text + end)\n\n            result = main([\"--difficulty\", \"easy\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n\n            self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n            output_str = \"\".join(outputs)\n            self.assertIn(\"🌻 Bloom!\", output_str)\n            self.assertIn(\"The garden is thriving.\", output_str)\n        finally:\n            random.choice = original_choice\n\n    def test_end_to_end_win_ascii(self):\n        \"\"\"E2E: scripted win game in ASCII mode.\"\"\"\n        original_choice = random.choice\n\n        def seeded_choice(seq):\n            rng = random.Random(42)\n            return rng.choice(seq)\n\n        random.choice = seeded_choice\n        try:\n            state = new_game(\"easy\")\n            guesses = sorted(set(state.secret_word))\n\n            outputs = []\n            guess_iter = iter(guesses)\n\n            def fake_input():\n                try:\n                    return next(guess_iter)\n                except StopIteration:\n                    raise EOFError()\n\n            def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n                outputs.append(text + end)\n\n            result = main([\"--ascii\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n\n            self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n            output_str = \"\".join(outputs)\n            self.assertNotIn(\"💧\", output_str)\n            self.assertNotIn(\"🌻\", output_str)\n            self.assertIn(\"* Bloom!\", output_str)\n        finally:\n            random.choice = original_choice","newString":"class TestMainEndToEndWin(unittest.TestCase):\n    \"\"\"Test a full game loop that ends in a win.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_end_to_end_win(self):\n        \"\"\"E2E: scripted win game shows final screen.\"\"\"\n        outputs = []\n\n        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n            outputs.append(text)\n\n        def fake_input_gen():\n            all_letters = \"ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ\"\n            for letter in all_letters:\n                yield letter\n\n        inputs = fake_input_gen()\n\n        def fake_input():\n            try:\n                letter = next(inputs)\n                return letter\n            except StopIteration:\n                raise EOFError()\n\n        result = main([\"--difficulty\", \"easy\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n\n        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n        output_str = \"\\n\".join(outputs)\n        self.assertIn(\"🌻 Bloom!\", output_str)\n        self.assertIn(\"The garden is thriving.\", output_str)\n\n    def test_end_to_end_win_ascii(self):\n        \"\"\"E2E: scripted win game in ASCII mode.\"\"\"\n        outputs = []\n\n        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n            outputs.append(text)\n\n        def fake_input_gen():\n            all_letters = \"ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ\"\n            for letter in all_letters:\n                yield letter\n\n        inputs = fake_input_gen()\n\n        def fake_input():\n            try:\n                letter = next(inputs)\n                return letter\n            except StopIteration:\n                raise EOFError()\n\n        result = main([\"--ascii\", \"--difficulty\", \"easy\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n\n        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n        output_str = \"\\n\".join(outputs)\n        self.assertNotIn(\"💧\", output_str)\n        self.assertNotIn(\"🌻\", output_str)\n        self.assertIn(\"* Bloom!\", output_str)","originalFile":"import random\nimport unittest\nfrom io import StringIO\n\nfrom word_garden.game import GameState, new_game\nfrom word_garden.ui import render, win_screen, loss_screen\nfrom word_garden.main import main\n\n\nclass TestRender(unittest.TestCase):\n    \"\"\"Test the render() function for both emoji and ASCII modes.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_render_emoji_at_start(self):\n        \"\"\"Emoji render includes title, word, water, weeds, growth glyph.\"\"\"\n        state = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters=set(),\n            remaining_water=6,\n            weed_count=0,\n            max_water=6,\n            status_message=\"\",\n            game_over=False,\n            won=False,\n        )\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n        self.assertIn(\"🌱 Word Garden\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"_ _ _ _ _ _\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"Guessed:\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"Water: 6/6 💧💧💧💧💧💧\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"Weeds: 0\", output)\n\n    def test_render_emoji_with_guesses(self):\n        \"\"\"Emoji render shows guessed letters sorted.\"\"\"\n        state = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"A\", \"R\", \"E\"},\n            remaining_water=6,\n            weed_count=0,\n            max_water=6,\n            status_message=\"Good guess!\",\n            game_over=False,\n            won=False,\n        )\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n        self.assertIn(\"_ A R _ E _\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"Guessed:  A E R\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"Good guess!\", output)\n\n    def test_render_ascii_no_emoji(self):\n        \"\"\"ASCII render contains no emoji characters.\"\"\"\n        state = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"A\", \"R\"},\n            remaining_water=4,\n            weed_count=2,\n            max_water=6,\n            status_message=\"\",\n            game_over=False,\n            won=False,\n        )\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertNotIn(\"💧\", output)\n        self.assertNotIn(\"🌿\", output)\n        self.assertNotIn(\"🌱\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"Water: 4/6 [****]\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"Weeds: 2 [--]\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"*\", output)  # ASCII plant\n\n    def test_render_emoji_progress_stage(self):\n        \"\"\"Emoji render shows progress glyph when some letters guessed.\"\"\"\n        state = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"A\", \"R\", \"D\"},\n            remaining_water=6,\n            weed_count=0,\n            max_water=6,\n            status_message=\"\",\n            game_over=False,\n            won=False,\n        )\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n        self.assertIn(\"🌿 Word Garden\", output)\n\n    def test_render_emoji_near_win_stage(self):\n        \"\"\"Emoji render shows near-win glyph when almost all letters guessed.\"\"\"\n        state = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\"},\n            remaining_water=6,\n            weed_count=0,\n            max_water=6,\n            status_message=\"\",\n            game_over=False,\n            won=False,\n        )\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n        self.assertIn(\"🌷 Word Garden\", output)\n\n    def test_render_with_status_message(self):\n        \"\"\"Render includes status message on its own line.\"\"\"\n        state = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters=set(),\n            remaining_water=6,\n            weed_count=0,\n            max_water=6,\n            status_message=\"No match. A weed appears.\",\n            game_over=False,\n            won=False,\n        )\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=False)\n        self.assertIn(\"No match. A weed appears.\", output)\n\n    def test_render_ascii_water_count(self):\n        \"\"\"ASCII mode shows water count with label.\"\"\"\n        state = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters=set(),\n            remaining_water=3,\n            weed_count=0,\n            max_water=6,\n            status_message=\"\",\n            game_over=False,\n            won=False,\n        )\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"Water: 3/6\", output)\n\n\nclass TestWinScreen(unittest.TestCase):\n    \"\"\"Test the win_screen() function.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_win_screen_emoji(self):\n        \"\"\"Win screen shows bloom emoji, word, and thriving message.\"\"\"\n        state = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\", \"N\"},\n            remaining_water=6,\n            weed_count=0,\n            max_water=6,\n            status_message=\"You guessed the word: GARDEN. The garden is thriving.\",\n            game_over=True,\n            won=True,\n        )\n        output = win_screen(state, ascii_mode=False)\n        self.assertIn(\"🌻 Bloom!\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"You guessed the word: GARDEN\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"The garden is thriving.\", output)\n\n    def test_win_screen_ascii_no_emoji(self):\n        \"\"\"Win screen ASCII contains no emoji.\"\"\"\n        state = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\", \"N\"},\n            remaining_water=6,\n            weed_count=0,\n            max_water=6,\n            status_message=\"\",\n            game_over=True,\n            won=True,\n        )\n        output = win_screen(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertNotIn(\"🌻\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"* Bloom!\", output)\n\n\nclass TestLossScreen(unittest.TestCase):\n    \"\"\"Test the loss_screen() function.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_loss_screen_emoji(self):\n        \"\"\"Loss screen shows wilted emoji, word, and try-again message.\"\"\"\n        state = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"A\", \"Z\"},\n            remaining_water=0,\n            weed_count=6,\n            max_water=6,\n            status_message=\"The garden ran out of water. The word was: GARDEN.\",\n            game_over=True,\n            won=False,\n        )\n        output = loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=False)\n        self.assertIn(\"🥀 The garden ran out of water.\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"The word was: GARDEN\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"Try again and grow a new garden.\", output)\n\n    def test_loss_screen_ascii_no_emoji(self):\n        \"\"\"Loss screen ASCII contains no emoji.\"\"\"\n        state = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"A\", \"Z\"},\n            remaining_water=0,\n            weed_count=6,\n            max_water=6,\n            status_message=\"\",\n            game_over=True,\n            won=False,\n        )\n        output = loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertNotIn(\"🥀\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"* The garden ran out of water.\", output)\n\n\nclass TestMainEndToEndWin(unittest.TestCase):\n    \"\"\"Test a full game loop that ends in a win.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_end_to_end_win(self):\n        \"\"\"E2E: scripted win game shows final screen.\"\"\"\n        import word_garden.words as words_module\n\n        original_choice = random.choice\n\n        def seeded_choice(seq):\n            rng = random.Random(42)\n            return rng.choice(seq)\n\n        random.choice = seeded_choice\n        try:\n            state = new_game(\"easy\")\n            guesses = sorted(set(state.secret_word))\n\n            outputs = []\n            guess_iter = iter(guesses)\n\n            def fake_input():\n                try:\n                    return next(guess_iter)\n                except StopIteration:\n                    raise EOFError()\n\n            def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n                outputs.append(text + end)\n\n            result = main([\"--difficulty\", \"easy\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n\n            self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n            output_str = \"\".join(outputs)\n            self.assertIn(\"🌻 Bloom!\", output_str)\n            self.assertIn(\"The garden is thriving.\", output_str)\n        finally:\n            random.choice = original_choice\n\n    def test_end_to_end_win_ascii(self):\n        \"\"\"E2E: scripted win game in ASCII mode.\"\"\"\n        original_choice = random.choice\n\n        def seeded_choice(seq):\n            rng = random.Random(42)\n            return rng.choice(seq)\n\n        random.choice = seeded_choice\n        try:\n            state = new_game(\"easy\")\n            guesses = sorted(set(state.secret_word))\n\n            outputs = []\n            guess_iter = iter(guesses)\n\n            def fake_input():\n                try:\n                    return next(guess_iter)\n                except StopIteration:\n                    raise EOFError()\n\n            def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n                outputs.append(text + end)\n\n            result = main([\"--ascii\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n\n            self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n            output_str = \"\".join(outputs)\n            self.assertNotIn(\"💧\", output_str)\n            self.assertNotIn(\"🌻\", output_str)\n            self.assertIn(\"* Bloom!\", output_str)\n        finally:\n            random.choice = original_choice\n\n\nclass TestMainEndToEndLoss(unittest.TestCase):\n    \"\"\"Test a full game loop that ends in a loss.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_end_to_end_loss(self):\n        \"\"\"E2E: scripted loss game shows final screen.\"\"\"\n        original_choice = random.choice\n\n        def seeded_choice(seq):\n            rng = random.Random(99)\n            return rng.choice(seq)\n\n        random.choice = seeded_choice\n        try:\n            state = new_game(\"easy\")\n\n            guesses = [\n                letter for letter in \"ZYXWVUTSRQPONMLKJIHGFEDCBA\"\n                if letter not in state.secret_word\n            ][:9]\n\n            outputs = []\n            guess_iter = iter(guesses)\n\n            def fake_input():\n                try:\n                    return next(guess_iter)\n                except StopIteration:\n                    raise EOFError()\n\n            def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n                outputs.append(text + end)\n\n            result = main([\"--difficulty\", \"easy\"], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n\n            self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n            output_str = \"\".join(outputs)\n            self.assertIn(\"🥀 The garden ran out of water.\", output_str)\n            self.assertIn(\"Try again and grow a new garden.\", output_str)\n        finally:\n            random.choice = original_choice\n\n\nclass TestMainInvalidInputRePrompt(unittest.TestCase):\n    \"\"\"Test that invalid input re-prompts without consuming a turn.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_invalid_then_valid(self):\n        \"\"\"Invalid input should re-prompt; valid input should advance.\"\"\"\n        rng = random.Random(42)\n        state = new_game(\"normal\", rng=rng)\n\n        guesses = [\"\", \"A\"] + sorted(state.secret_word)[1:]\n\n        outputs = []\n        guess_iter = iter(guesses)\n\n        def fake_input():\n            try:\n                return next(guess_iter)\n            except StopIteration:\n                raise EOFError()\n\n        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n            outputs.append(text + end)\n\n        result = main([], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n\n        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n        output_str = \"\".join(outputs)\n        self.assertIn(\"Please enter a single letter.\", output_str)\n        self.assertIn(\"Good guess! The garden grows.\", output_str)\n\n\nclass TestMainEOFGracefulExit(unittest.TestCase):\n    \"\"\"Test that EOF (Ctrl-D) exits gracefully.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_eof_exit_code(self):\n        \"\"\"EOF should return exit code 0.\"\"\"\n        outputs = []\n\n        def fake_input():\n            raise EOFError()\n\n        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n            outputs.append(text + end)\n\n        result = main([], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n\n        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n        output_str = \"\".join(outputs)\n        self.assertIn(\"Goodbye\", output_str)\n\n\nclass TestMainKeyboardInterruptGracefulExit(unittest.TestCase):\n    \"\"\"Test that Ctrl-C exits gracefully.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_keyboard_interrupt_exit_code(self):\n        \"\"\"KeyboardInterrupt should return exit code 0.\"\"\"\n        outputs = []\n\n        def fake_input():\n            raise KeyboardInterrupt()\n\n        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):\n            outputs.append(text + end)\n\n        result = main([], input_fn=fake_input, output_fn=fake_print)\n\n        self.assertEqual(result, 0)\n        output_str = \"\".join(outputs)\n        self.assertIn(\"Goodbye\", output_str)\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":206,"oldLines":76,"newStart":206,"newLines":62,"lines":[" ","     def test_end_to_end_win(self):","         \"\"\"E2E: scripted win game shows final screen.\"\"\"","-        import word_garden.words as words_module","+        outputs = []"," ","-        original_choice = random.choice","+        def fake_print(text, end=\"\\n\"):","+            outputs.append(text)"," ","-        def seeded_choice(seq):","-            rng = random.Random(42)","-            return rng.choice(seq)","+        def fake_input_gen():","+            all_letters = \"ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ\"","+            for letter in all_letters:","+                yield letter"," ","-        random.choice = seeded_choice","-        try:","-            state = new_game(\"easy\")","-            guesses = sorted(set(state.secret_word))","+        inputs = fake_input_gen()"," ","-            outputs = []","-            guess_iter = iter(guesses)","+        def fake_input():","+            try:","+                letter = next(inputs)","+                return letter","+            except StopIteration:","+                raise EOFError()"," ","-            def fake_input():","-                try:","-                    return next(guess_iter)","-                except StopIterati